      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/2/2/7",
      "text": [
        " : قُلْتُ لِأَبِي عَبْدِ اَللَّهِ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ - جُعِلْتُ فِدَاكَ يَسْتَقْرِضُ اَلرَّجُلُ وَ يَحُجُّ قَالَ \"نَعَمْ\"\nقُلْتُ يَسْتَقْرِضُ وَ يَتَزَوَّجُ قَالَ \"نَعَمْ إِنَّهُ يَنْتَظِرُ رِزْقَ اَللَّهِ غُدْوَةً وَ عَشِيَّةً\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.3685 - Al-Mithami narrated from Abu Musa who said:\nI said to Abu Abdillah (as)-\"May I be your ransom! Can a man borrow and perform Hajj?\"\nImam (as) said: \"Yes.\"\nI said: \"Can he borrow and get married?\"\nImam (as) said: \"Yes, for he awaits the provision of Allah (swt) morning and evening.\""
        ]
      }
    },
